Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Trim the @aubergine{2}, halve lengthways and chop into 2cm wide strips, then chop into 2cm chunks. Pop the potato wedges on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Put the aubergine chunks on another baking tray, drizzle with @oil{} (no need to season). Toss to coat.

Roast the wedges on the top shelf of the oven until golden and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Roast the aubergine on the middle shelf of your oven until browned and tender as well, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn the aubergine and potatoes after ~{15%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Pop half the red onion in a #small bowl{} and add the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the pickle. Add a pinch of salt, mix together and set aside.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1/2}, halve lengthways, thinly slice. Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Mix the @miso paste{15%g}, @honey{15%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @water{1%tbsp} per person and @sugar{1/2%tsp} together in a small bowl.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). When hot, add the @sesame seeds{15%g}, toast until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Toss every minute. Pop half of them in another small bowl and add the other half to the miso soy mixture. Stir the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} in the bowl with the sesame seeds (not the miso bowl!).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a frying pan on medium high heat. Add the red onion, stir fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, add the roasted aubergine to the pan with the onion. Pour the miso mix into the pan. Bubble away until the moisture has gone and the aubergine is sticky, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from the heat. Pop your @plain taco tortillas{6} into the oven to warm through for the last ~{2-3%minutes} of the wedges cooking time.

Spoon the sesame mayo onto the bottom of each taco and spread it out. Divide the lettuce between the tacos and squeeze on some lime juice. Spoon the aubergine mixture on top, followed by a sprinkle of coriander and the pickled onion. Serve with the wedges on the side and cut the remaining lime into wedges to serve alongside. Enjoy!